OL,6,FAlthough repairs were made to pipe,
OL,7,FNRW officers were called to further
OL,8,Fincidents at the site in March and May
OL,9,F2023, and also on January 2024.
OL,11,FDwr Cymru Welsh Water was been fined
OL,12,F#90,000 for the the Gwent levels
OL,13,Fincidents, and a further #160,000 for
OL,14,Fan incident on a tributary of the Afon
OL,15,FLlwyd at Herberts Wood, Pontnewynydd.
OL,17,FIn the latter incident, in February
OL,18,F2023, the source was a spillage from a
OL,19,Ffoul sewer chamber.
